  "displayField": "OBJECTID",
  "description": "The Shore-to-Core-to-Shore TIF District declares improvements to parcels of real property that fall within that district boundaries to be a public purpose and exempt from taxation describing the public infrastructure improvements to be made to directly benefit the district, requiring the owners of the improvements on such parcels to make service payments in lieu of taxes, providing for the distribution of those service payments to the Cleveland Municipal School District and to one or more funds established by the City to hold those service payments, to determine public improvement needs of the District. Existing TIF parcels in this geography, are NOT included in this district (see link below). The Shore-to-Core-to-Shore TIF District should create, capture, and leverage growth in Cleveland’s Downtown and the near west side to support robust public infrastructure investments, that strengthen waterfronts and Downtown, and fund investments in parks, recreation, and neighborhood investments throughout Cleveland’s neighborhoods. For further detail refer to https://www.clevelandcitycouncil.org/pdf/web/viewer.html?file=/sites/default/files/2024-04/City%20Record%20-%204-5-24.pdfDocumentation and Definitions: TIF Definition: https://development.ohio.gov/business/state-incentives/tax-increment-financingUpdate Frequency: As neededContact: City of Cleveland Economic Development ",
